Rudder Travel Limit Rigging and Hydraulic Stop Check

ATA Chapters: 27 – Flight Controls + 29 – Hydraulic Power
S1000D DMC: 27-40-00-06-00A-720A-P

This task is performed:

    - After rudder actuator replacement or hydraulic circuit modification

    - After flight control computer updates affecting authority or bias

    - Following structural repair to vertical stabilizer or rudder mount points

    - During scheduled maintenance check intervals (MPD referenced)

