  <content>
    <procedure>
      <taskRequirement>
        <skillRequirement>Flight Control Mechanic</skillRequirement>
        <skillRequirement>Hydraulics Technician</skillRequirement>
        <timeRequirement>4.0 hours</timeRequirement>
        <crewRequirement>3 Personnel (Flight control rigging team)</crewRequirement>
      </taskRequirement>

      <preliminaryRqmts>
        <preliminaryRqmtsDescr>Aircraft parked, wheels chocked, hydraulic systems A, B, and C fully pressurized. Flight control system initialized in TEST mode via CMS. Vertical stabilizer access panels (ZONE 450) removed.</preliminaryRqmtsDescr>

        <safety>
          <warning>
            Movement of the rudder actuator under hydraulic pressure is forceful. Ensure personnel are clear of rudder arc before commanding motion.
          </warning>
          <caution>
            Do not manually force rudder surfaces against hard stops. All movements must be powered by hydraulic system to avoid structural damage.
          </caution>
          <note>
            Use calibrated digital inclinometer for precise rudder angle measurement. Maximum tolerance between mechanical stop and hydraulic stop is ±0.1°.
          </note>
        </safety>
      </preliminaryRqmts>

      <mainProcedure>
        <step>
          <para>Connect CMS maintenance terminal. Select FLIGHT CONTROL SURFACE MONITOR (RUDDER) screen.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Command rudder full LEFT deflection. Measure travel angle relative to aircraft centerline using inclinometer mounted on rudder trailing edge.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Verify full LEFT travel meets nominal specification: 30.0° ± 0.2°. Confirm actuator contacts hydraulic stop without overtravel into mechanical stop.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Command rudder full RIGHT deflection. Measure and verify full RIGHT travel meets nominal specification: 25.0° ± 0.2°.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Cycle rudder from center to full stops (left and right) 5 times. Observe CMS position feedback curve for linearity and absence of lag or spikes.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Inspect rudder actuator attachment points for security. Check for leaks, structural deformation, and correct torque values per AMM 27-40-00.</para>
        </step>
      </mainProcedure>

      <closeProcedure>
        <step>
          <para>Restore flight control mode to NORMAL via CMS. Reinstall all removed access panels. Remove all locks, tags, and test equipment.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Record travel limit readings, synchronization results, actuator health, and any anomalies in aircraft maintenance record (ATA 05-00-00).</para>
        </step>
      </closeProcedure>

